</bibRefCitation>
indicated that the 
<typeStatus id="83188837FFD92E127114FA55FCC8DEB3" box="[844,894,1444,1470]" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">type</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="9BA34D16FFD92E1271F4FA55FBEFDEB0" box="[940,1113,1444,1469]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Platyopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="101" pageNumber="102" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maroccanus">
<emphasis id="6ED7EA87FFD92E1271F4FA55FBEFDEB0" box="[940,1113,1444,1469]" italics="true" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">P. maroccanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was deposited in the Madrid Museum, but I found the male 
<typeStatus id="83188837FFD92E12715EFA3DFCDBDEEB" box="[774,877,1484,1510]" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">holotype</typeStatus>
and a female 
<typeStatus id="83188837FFD92E12764FFA3DFBCADEEB" box="[1047,1148,1484,1510]" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">paratype</typeStatus>
in the 
<collectionCode id="3AB2AE50FFD92E127689FA3DFA9DDEEB" box="[1233,1323,1484,1510]" country="France" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34988" name="Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">MNHN</collectionCode>
along with a male and female from Arris, 
<collectingCountry id="24B47605FFD92E1270ACFA05FCE6DD03" box="[756,848,1524,1550]" name="Algeria" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">Algeria</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
